com.payleven.payment.api

Class PaylevenApi

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.payleven.payment.api.PaylevenApi

  • public class PaylevenApi
extends Object
    This api allows you to use the payleven app to do payments. Using the payleven app from within your own app is a two step process

    Step 1 - Issue a request

    you issue an request to the payleven app by using one of static the helper methods from this class

    1. To start a payment use initiatePayment

    2. To open the sales history use openSalesHistory

    3. To starts a refund use openTransactionDetails. The app will not immediatly start a refund but will open up a detail view of the transaction instead. The user must then confirm the refund by explicitly pressing the refund button

    Step 2 - Handling the response

    Responses to requests will be received in onActivityResult

    1. Overide onActivityResult in your Activity
    2. Implement the interface PaylevenResponseListener
    3. use handleIntent to parse the parameters from onActivityResult
    4. handleIntent will call one of the methods from your PaylevenResponseListener

    Example 

     @Override
 protected void onActivityResult(int requestCode, int resultCode, Intent data) {
     super.onActivityResult(requestCode, resultCode, data);
     PaylevenApi.handleIntent(requestCode, data, new PaylevenResponseListener() {
         
         @Override
         public void onPaymentFinished(String orderId, TransactionRequest originalRequest, Map<String, String> result, PaymentCompletedStatus status) {
             // payment finished, check status                
         }
         
         @Override
         public void onNoPaylevenResponse(Intent data) {
             // intent data was not sent by payleven                
         }
         
         @Override
         public void onOpenTransactionDetailsFinished(String orderId, Map<String, String> transactionData, OpenTransactionDetailsCompletedStatus status) {
             // refund finished, check status                
             
         }
         
         @Override
         public void onOpenSalesHistoryFinished() {
             // sales history finished                
             
         }
     });
 }
